# Merge policy for the git-as-database setup (see docs/LAB_REVIEW.md C4).
#
# The VM capture daemon, the local research cycle, and interactive sessions all push to
# this repo concurrently. git_sync.sh used to pass `-X union` GLOBALLY, which union-merges
# every conflicting file. That is correct ONLY for append-only event streams (both sides'
# appended lines survive). For full-rewrite single-object files it CONCATENATES the two
# versions into invalid JSON / interleaved markdown. So union is scoped here per-path, and
# `-X union` was removed from git_sync.sh.

# Append-only event streams → union-merge (concurrent appends both survive).
data/**/*.jsonl merge=union

# Everything else uses the DEFAULT merge. In particular the full-rewrite single-object
# files below must NOT union-merge — a real conflict there must produce conflict markers
# (which aborts the rebase in git_sync.sh) instead of silently corrupting:
#   data/games/*/meta.json, strategy_params.json, docs/*.html, docs/*.md
# These are listed explicitly as a guard in case a broad union attr is ever re-added.
**/meta.json   merge=text
strategy_params.json merge=text
docs/**        merge=text

# The durable corpus is gzipped → binary; never attempt a text/union merge.
*.gz binary
